1
00:01:44,370 --> 00:01:45,572
All right, countdown.

2
00:01:46,473 --> 00:01:47,106
Five.

3
00:01:47,507 --> 00:01:48,308
Four.

4
00:01:48,675 --> 00:01:49,476
Three.

5
00:01:49,776 --> 00:01:50,477
Two.

6
00:01:50,877 --> 00:01:51,611
One.

7
00:01:51,845 --> 00:01:54,514
Happy New Year!

8
00:02:06,626 --> 00:02:07,961
Happy New Year!

9
00:02:08,361 --> 00:02:09,162
Happy New Year!

10
00:02:09,229 --> 00:02:10,129
Happy New Year!

11
00:02:10,964 --> 00:02:11,965
Happy New Year!

12
00:02:15,034 --> 00:02:15,802
Happy New Year!

13
00:02:37,824 --> 00:02:39,125
Hello, everyone. I'm Lin Yi.

14
00:02:39,792 --> 00:02:41,027
I'm new here. Please take care of me.

15
00:02:41,294 --> 00:02:42,629
Surgery or no surgery, let's work together.

16
00:02:47,167 --> 00:02:47,600
Narrow-minded.

17
00:02:47,800 --> 00:02:48,201
Traitor.

18
00:02:48,635 --> 00:02:49,169
So dramatic.

19
00:02:49,302 --> 00:02:49,702
Traitor.

20
00:02:49,836 --> 00:02:50,470
Putting on airs.

21
00:02:50,570 --> 00:02:51,271
Traitor.

22
00:02:51,404 --> 00:02:51,905
Traitor.

23
00:02:52,005 --> 00:02:53,039
Is that the only word you know?

24
00:02:53,173 --> 00:02:53,873
I know plenty.

25
00:02:53,873 --> 00:02:54,874
This one just suits you best.

26
00:02:54,874 --> 00:02:55,308
Traitor.

27
00:02:58,311 --> 00:02:59,345
What are you grinning about?

28
00:03:00,079 --> 00:03:01,414
You're the smart one, huh?

29
00:03:01,714 --> 00:03:02,916
Hobbit.

30
00:03:03,550 --> 00:03:04,784
Who's a hobbit?

31
00:03:05,118 --> 00:03:05,685
You.

32
00:03:06,085 --> 00:03:07,954
Then you're the Hulk.

33
00:03:09,088 --> 00:03:10,423
I carefully coordinated this outfit

34
00:03:10,523 --> 00:03:11,591
just to come out with you.

35
00:03:11,624 --> 00:03:12,492
Green.

36
00:03:41,254 --> 00:03:42,255
In the new year,

37
00:03:43,489 --> 00:03:44,157
Director Zhou,

38
00:03:46,726 --> 00:03:48,628
I hope you'll continue to look after me.

39
00:03:51,331 --> 00:03:52,031
Manager Ouyang,

40
00:03:53,566 --> 00:03:54,234
I look forward to working with you.

41
00:03:54,767 --> 00:03:55,235
I wish you

42
00:03:55,969 --> 00:03:56,703
greater success every day.

43
00:03:58,972 --> 00:04:00,506
I wish everything goes your way,

44
00:04:01,574 --> 00:04:03,142
and that all your patients stay healthy.

45
00:04:03,676 --> 00:04:05,011
I wish Senlin health and safety,

46
00:04:06,112 --> 00:04:06,913
and a happy childhood.

47
00:04:07,880 --> 00:04:09,082
I wish Professor Fang,

48
00:04:10,750 --> 00:04:12,185
Dr. Fang, and you

49
00:04:12,919 --> 00:04:13,686
a happy and complete family.

50
00:04:20,093 --> 00:04:20,793
I wish you happiness.

51
00:04:22,629 --> 00:04:23,796
And I wish you happiness too.

52
00:05:22,155 --> 00:05:22,922
Happy New Year.

53
00:05:23,790 --> 00:05:24,357
Professor,

54
00:05:52,118 --> 00:05:52,952
we still need to follow up again

55
00:05:53,052 --> 00:05:53,986
with Mr. Xiao in the lab.

56
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:54,854
All right, Dr. Fang.

57
00:06:00,927 --> 00:06:01,961
How do you feel today?

58
00:06:01,961 --> 00:06:02,562
Any better?

59
00:06:03,062 --> 00:06:03,596
A little.

60
00:06:05,164 --> 00:06:06,466
I didn't say it

61
00:06:06,532 --> 00:06:07,533
out of anger or impulse.

62
00:06:09,335 --> 00:06:10,770
I just feel exhausted.

63
00:06:12,839 --> 00:06:13,773
I really tried

64
00:06:13,806 --> 00:06:14,874
to be there for him.

65
00:06:16,042 --> 00:06:17,877
But every time I tried to communicate,

66
00:06:18,311 --> 00:06:19,645
he chose to ignore me.

67
00:06:21,547 --> 00:06:23,649
And somehow, as long as he says sorry,

68
00:06:24,884 --> 00:06:26,352
I'm expected to say it's fine.

69
00:06:30,723 --> 00:06:31,824
I truly don't know

70
00:06:32,992 --> 00:06:34,193
how to be with him anymore.

71
00:06:36,863 --> 00:06:37,997
This life where I can't push too hard

72
00:06:37,997 --> 00:06:39,265
or tread too lightly

73
00:06:41,200 --> 00:06:42,201
is exhausting.

74
00:06:46,105 --> 00:06:48,708
Staying at Mom's lately

75
00:06:50,410 --> 00:06:52,011
finally let me breathe.

76
00:06:54,013 --> 00:06:54,614
Otherwise,

77
00:06:55,314 --> 00:06:56,649
I would've broken down.

78
00:06:57,917 --> 00:06:58,918
I have to save myself.

79
00:07:00,086 --> 00:07:00,953
Whatever you decide,

80
00:07:00,987 --> 00:07:01,854
I'll support you.

81
00:07:04,357 --> 00:07:05,825
Mom and I are both here for you.

82
00:07:08,628 --> 00:07:09,729
Keep looking forward.

83
00:07:19,505 --> 00:07:20,506
I have to get back to work.

84
00:07:38,791 --> 00:07:39,792
The winter hats and scarves—

85
00:07:39,792 --> 00:07:40,359
where are they?

86
00:07:45,631 --> 00:07:46,466
I don't know.

87
00:07:47,767 --> 00:07:48,668
Xiaoran said they're in

88
00:07:48,734 --> 00:07:49,836
a green storage box.

89
00:07:50,403 --> 00:07:51,003
I couldn't find it.

90
00:08:02,482 --> 00:08:03,182
What about the document pouch?

91
00:08:07,954 --> 00:08:08,487
I don't know.

92
00:08:12,492 --> 00:08:13,125
This home...

93
00:08:13,826 --> 00:08:14,760
What do you even know about it?

94
00:08:39,886 --> 00:08:40,519
This is the content plan

95
00:08:40,553 --> 00:08:42,188
for the upcoming videos.

96
00:08:42,522 --> 00:08:43,189
The final page

97
00:08:43,289 --> 00:08:45,091
has the account name

98
00:08:45,091 --> 00:08:45,524
and password for Cardiology Whirlwind.

99
00:08:46,125 --> 00:08:46,492
Okay.

100
00:08:47,693 --> 00:08:48,094
Director Zhou.

101
00:08:48,728 --> 00:08:49,095
You're here.

102
00:08:50,162 --> 00:08:50,630
Director.

103
00:08:51,964 --> 00:08:52,732
And these.

104
00:08:53,232 --> 00:08:54,634
This is the equipment for filming short videos.

105
00:08:54,734 --> 00:08:55,801
If there's anything you don't understand,

106
00:08:55,835 --> 00:08:56,736
ask me anytime.

107
00:08:57,236 --> 00:08:57,603
Okay.

108
00:08:58,037 --> 00:08:59,272
As for publicity

109
00:08:59,505 --> 00:09:00,606
and all this equipment,

110
00:09:00,640 --> 00:09:01,807
I'm really not very good at it.

111
00:09:02,108 --> 00:09:03,109
There may be a lot more

112
00:09:03,142 --> 00:09:03,843
I'll need to trouble

113
00:09:03,876 --> 00:09:04,710
Manager Ouyang with in the future.

114
00:09:05,478 --> 00:09:06,712
Let's add each other on WeChat.

115
00:09:08,281 --> 00:09:08,814
I'll scan yours.

116
00:09:12,251 --> 00:09:13,386
You two carry on. I'll get going.

117
00:09:14,186 --> 00:09:14,720
Thank you.

118
00:09:19,358 --> 00:09:19,926
Director.

119
00:09:21,093 --> 00:09:22,361
I can learn

120
00:09:22,395 --> 00:09:23,362
new professional knowledge.

121
00:09:23,429 --> 00:09:23,963
But

122
00:09:24,397 --> 00:09:25,331
when it comes to publicity, I...

123
00:09:28,601 --> 00:09:29,168
I'll do my best.

124
00:10:01,734 --> 00:10:02,268
Director Sheng.

125
00:10:02,668 --> 00:10:03,235
The comprehensive ICU

126
00:10:03,235 --> 00:10:04,303
for the medical consortium

127
00:10:04,403 --> 00:10:05,438
is in its final implementation stage.

128
00:10:05,871 --> 00:10:07,173
I'll need to stay there next week.

129
00:10:07,673 --> 00:10:08,240
For how long?

130
00:10:08,708 --> 00:10:09,408
About a week.

131
00:10:09,909 --> 00:10:10,543
A whole week?

132
00:10:11,243 --> 00:10:11,877
Then what about

133
00:10:11,877 --> 00:10:12,311
the comprehensive ICU here?

134
00:10:13,746 --> 00:10:15,815
I won't be at the consortium

135
00:10:15,848 --> 00:10:16,749
for the entire week.

136
00:10:17,149 --> 00:10:18,784
I'll come back every couple of days.

137
00:10:19,085 --> 00:10:20,853
And the head nurse, Xiao Du,

138
00:10:21,120 --> 00:10:21,954
Xiao Yang, Xiao Fan,

139
00:10:22,121 --> 00:10:23,456
and the other doctors are all here.

140
00:10:23,723 --> 00:10:24,890
It won't delay the work here.

141
00:10:25,491 --> 00:10:27,126
If you can dump everything on them,

142
00:10:27,159 --> 00:10:27,793
then what does

143
00:10:27,827 --> 00:10:28,394
the comprehensive ICU need you for?

144
00:10:32,465 --> 00:10:33,432
Tell me the truth.

145
00:10:34,600 --> 00:10:35,468
Is this because

146
00:10:36,402 --> 00:10:37,169
of what's going on with Lin Yi?

147
00:10:42,241 --> 00:10:42,808
Director Sheng.

148
00:10:43,542 --> 00:10:44,644
My going to the consortium

149
00:10:44,810 --> 00:10:46,212
and my relationship with Lin Yi

150
00:10:46,479 --> 00:10:47,313
are two separate matters.

151
00:10:47,613 --> 00:10:48,648
Separate matters?

152
00:10:49,649 --> 00:10:51,150
Last time I only mentioned

153
00:10:51,183 --> 00:10:52,051
Lin Yi's hair,

154
00:10:52,151 --> 00:10:53,119
and you got that worked up.

155
00:10:53,552 --> 00:10:54,653
I didn't understand it then.

156
00:10:55,488 --> 00:10:56,055
Dr. Fang,

157
00:10:56,989 --> 00:10:58,190
letting relationship problems

158
00:10:58,224 --> 00:10:58,991
affect your work

159
00:10:59,558 --> 00:11:01,160
is highly unprofessional.

160
00:11:05,331 --> 00:11:05,831
Director Sheng,

161
00:11:06,632 --> 00:11:09,168
jumping to conclusions without cause

162
00:11:09,568 --> 00:11:11,270
is also highly unprofessional.

163
00:11:17,410 --> 00:11:17,877
One week.

164
00:11:18,411 --> 00:11:19,078
Not a day more.

165
00:11:19,478 --> 00:11:20,079
Thank you, Director Sheng.

166
00:11:30,489 --> 00:11:32,491
Did Sister Xiaoran really break up with Director Lin?

167
00:11:33,325 --> 00:11:34,493
No way.

168
00:11:34,493 --> 00:11:35,194
Don't spread rumors.

169
00:11:35,361 --> 00:11:36,962
Look at Xiaoran's Moments lately.

170
00:11:37,363 --> 00:11:38,964
Director Lin hasn't liked a single post,

171
00:11:40,866 --> 00:11:41,634
or commented on any.

172
00:11:42,334 --> 00:11:43,502
Director Lin is usually

173
00:11:43,502 --> 00:11:44,270
pretty busy, isn't he?

174
00:11:44,303 --> 00:11:45,504
Not liking them is normal.

175
00:11:46,372 --> 00:11:47,306
The two of them—

176
00:11:47,640 --> 00:11:49,075
one is setting up an external hospital station,

177
00:11:49,208 --> 00:11:50,309
the other is working on the medical consortium.

178
00:11:50,810 --> 00:11:52,011
They hardly see each other.

179
00:11:52,545 --> 00:11:53,813
That is pretty risky.

180
00:11:54,413 --> 00:11:55,014
And Director Zhou's

181
00:11:55,014 --> 00:11:56,082
attitude toward Director Lin lately

182
00:11:56,082 --> 00:11:56,949
has been rather cool.

183
00:11:57,349 --> 00:11:59,085
Looks like Director Lin's position

184
00:11:59,151 --> 00:11:59,719
as his future brother-in-law is in danger.

185
00:12:00,352 --> 00:12:01,087
Director Zhou is always

186
00:12:01,087 --> 00:12:02,121
that way with everyone—

187
00:12:02,121 --> 00:12:03,055
neither warm nor cold.

188
00:12:03,255 --> 00:12:05,124
Maybe they interact where we can't see it.

189
00:12:06,392 --> 00:12:06,759
Right?

190
00:12:09,395 --> 00:12:10,029
We understand.

191
00:12:10,496 --> 00:12:12,198
We all understand how you feel.

192
00:12:12,965 --> 00:12:13,399
I understand too.

193
00:12:13,866 --> 00:12:15,000
What do you understand?

194
00:12:15,201 --> 00:12:16,035
That's just how it is.

195
00:12:16,035 --> 00:12:17,136
A little arguing

196
00:12:17,436 --> 00:12:19,004
is normal in a relationship.

197
00:12:21,907 --> 00:12:22,508
Anyway, this couple

198
00:12:22,575 --> 00:12:23,542
could never break up.

199
00:12:25,144 --> 00:12:26,145
Absolutely never.

200
00:12:27,279 --> 00:12:27,746
Impossible.

201
00:12:28,447 --> 00:12:28,881
Impossible.

202
00:12:32,184 --> 00:12:32,785
Confirmed.

203
00:12:33,152 --> 00:12:34,286
The Yi-Ran couple really split up.

204
00:12:34,553 --> 00:12:35,387
I got an anonymous tip

205
00:12:35,654 --> 00:12:36,355
and verified it with the people involved.

206
00:12:36,355 --> 00:12:37,289
Lin Yi has been much quieter

207
00:12:37,289 --> 00:12:37,823
in surgery these past two days.

208
00:12:37,823 --> 00:12:38,891
They were together over two years, right?

209
00:12:39,024 --> 00:12:39,592
They really broke up.

210
00:12:40,359 --> 00:12:41,360
Little Sunshine is so wonderful.

211
00:12:41,627 --> 00:12:43,162
Lin Yi didn't know how lucky he was.

212
00:12:43,229 --> 00:12:44,363
Little Sunshine

213
00:12:44,363 --> 00:12:45,464
hasn't smiled at all lately.

214
00:12:45,598 --> 00:12:46,599
She seems dimmer.

215
00:12:57,409 --> 00:12:57,843
Dr. Fang.

216
00:12:58,544 --> 00:12:59,678
I brought you milk tea.

217
00:13:00,312 --> 00:13:01,046
Thank you.

218
00:13:01,347 --> 00:13:02,615
Did you just get back from the consortium?

219
00:13:03,015 --> 00:13:04,383
Yes. The wrap-up work there

220
00:13:04,450 --> 00:13:05,384
is pretty complicated.

221
00:13:06,519 --> 00:13:07,052
Dr. Fang,

222
00:13:07,653 --> 00:13:08,788
this is my paper.

223
00:13:09,088 --> 00:13:09,889
I'm preparing to submit it.

224
00:13:10,389 --> 00:13:11,290
It's finished.

225
00:13:11,590 --> 00:13:12,391
Congratulations.

226
00:13:15,928 --> 00:13:16,829
"I dedicate this paper

227
00:13:16,829 --> 00:13:17,797
to my most respected mentor,

228
00:13:17,797 --> 00:13:18,731
Ms. Fang Xiaoran."

229
00:13:18,831 --> 00:13:19,465
What's this?

230
00:13:20,399 --> 00:13:21,000
I wrote

231
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:21,801
a special acknowledgment for you.

232
00:13:25,671 --> 00:13:27,239
It sounds like it's written

233
00:13:27,273 --> 00:13:28,908
for a late teacher.

234
00:13:29,308 --> 00:13:29,808
No, no.

235
00:13:29,909 --> 00:13:30,743
That's not what I meant.

236
00:13:30,743 --> 00:13:31,277
I just

237
00:13:31,811 --> 00:13:33,445
wanted to express my gratitude

238
00:13:33,479 --> 00:13:34,713
for all your help.

239
00:13:35,214 --> 00:13:36,448
And I also hope

240
00:13:37,650 --> 00:13:38,918
you won't be sad

241
00:13:39,752 --> 00:13:40,319
because of that thing.

242
00:13:41,353 --> 00:13:42,121
What thing?

243
00:13:43,756 --> 00:13:44,490
You know...

244
00:13:50,529 --> 00:13:51,964
I appreciate the thought.

245
00:13:52,731 --> 00:13:53,599
But this paper

246
00:13:53,632 --> 00:13:55,034
is something you worked hard on.

247
00:13:55,067 --> 00:13:56,468
There's no need to mention me.

248
00:13:57,436 --> 00:13:58,470
But Dr. Fang...

249
00:13:58,671 --> 00:13:59,205
Otherwise,

250
00:13:59,205 --> 00:14:00,272
every time I see your paper,

251
00:14:00,272 --> 00:14:01,106
I'll remember

252
00:14:01,273 --> 00:14:02,441
that you broke up.

253
00:14:03,642 --> 00:14:03,976
Sorry.

254
00:14:04,043 --> 00:14:05,711
Dr. Fang, I didn't think it through.

255
00:14:06,345 --> 00:14:06,946
It's fine.

256
00:14:07,279 --> 00:14:07,913
Your Dr. Fang

257
00:14:07,913 --> 00:14:09,415
isn't that easy to defeat.

258
00:14:11,850 --> 00:14:12,384
Go back to work.

259
00:14:13,953 --> 00:14:14,753
Take care of yourself.

260
00:14:15,087 --> 00:14:15,721
I'll get going.

261
00:14:26,398 --> 00:14:26,932
Xiaofeng,

262
00:14:27,399 --> 00:14:28,567
I asked you here today

263
00:14:28,634 --> 00:14:29,768
to tell you

264
00:14:29,869 --> 00:14:30,669
that the hospital has decided

265
00:14:31,270 --> 00:14:34,039
to begin selecting

266
00:14:34,173 --> 00:14:34,974
a director for the Heart Center.

267
00:14:38,043 --> 00:14:39,245
The position has remained vacant.

268
00:14:39,612 --> 00:14:40,412
The reason I

269
00:14:40,412 --> 00:14:41,714
never took it on concurrently

270
00:14:41,914 --> 00:14:43,649
was that I wanted to leave these opportunities

271
00:14:43,916 --> 00:14:44,884
to outstanding

272
00:14:44,917 --> 00:14:46,085
young people like you.

273
00:14:48,153 --> 00:14:49,722
And this time, the Party Committee has decided

274
00:14:50,022 --> 00:14:51,090
that the center director

275
00:14:51,423 --> 00:14:52,725
will have authority over the center

276
00:14:52,725 --> 00:14:54,560
and its subordinate departments,

277
00:14:55,294 --> 00:14:56,595
including personnel and finances.

278
00:14:58,397 --> 00:14:59,565
After discussion,

279
00:15:00,032 --> 00:15:01,233
the Party Committee's candidates

280
00:15:01,634 --> 00:15:02,268
are you

281
00:15:03,269 --> 00:15:04,803
and Sheng Nian.

282
00:15:09,008 --> 00:15:10,542
So the big news

283
00:15:10,609 --> 00:15:11,543
finally dropped.

284
00:15:11,610 --> 00:15:12,077
Right?

285
00:15:12,444 --> 00:15:13,312
Finally.

286
00:15:13,879 --> 00:15:14,947
Isn't it too soon?

287
00:15:15,814 --> 00:15:17,349
They're ten years apart in seniority.

288
00:15:17,449 --> 00:15:18,050
And

289
00:15:18,284 --> 00:15:19,118
Director Zhou is currently

290
00:15:19,118 --> 00:15:20,319
only an acting director.

291
00:15:20,753 --> 00:15:21,353
So,

292
00:15:21,787 --> 00:15:22,521
the outcome

293
00:15:22,922 --> 00:15:24,323
is basically obvious.

294
00:15:24,823 --> 00:15:25,791
Not necessarily.

295
00:15:26,325 --> 00:15:27,893
A lot of hospitals now emphasize

296
00:15:27,960 --> 00:15:29,328
younger management talent.

297
00:15:29,561 --> 00:15:30,663
I heard in the news recently

298
00:15:31,430 --> 00:15:32,731
that some district in Dongjiang—

299
00:15:32,798 --> 00:15:33,599
I forget which one—

300
00:15:33,732 --> 00:15:34,800
had a central hospital

301
00:15:35,134 --> 00:15:37,169
promote someone born in the '90s to vice president.

302
00:15:37,436 --> 00:15:38,637
That was a secondary hospital.

303
00:15:38,904 --> 00:15:39,805
It's different from ours.

304
00:15:40,039 --> 00:15:41,674
I also heard a rumor

305
00:15:42,174 --> 00:15:42,808
that

306
00:15:43,175 --> 00:15:44,109
this proposal

307
00:15:44,143 --> 00:15:45,744
came from President Wang.

308
00:15:46,111 --> 00:15:48,213
Some other hospital leaders

309
00:15:48,247 --> 00:15:49,348
also strongly support it.

310
00:15:49,848 --> 00:15:50,349
Then it's over.

311
00:15:50,983 --> 00:15:51,450
Totally over.

312
00:15:52,051 --> 00:15:52,985
Director Sheng

313
00:15:53,252 --> 00:15:55,054
was President Wang's student before.

314
00:15:55,354 --> 00:15:56,522
At their former hospital,

315
00:15:57,122 --> 00:15:57,756
Director Sheng

316
00:15:57,790 --> 00:15:58,624
was also personally

317
00:15:58,791 --> 00:16:00,092
promoted by President Wang.

318
00:16:00,359 --> 00:16:01,527
Then isn't this completely hopeless?

319
00:16:01,827 --> 00:16:03,162
Director Zhou has no chance at all.

320
00:16:09,635 --> 00:16:10,035
Come in.

321
00:16:11,437 --> 00:16:11,837
Brother.

322
00:16:12,571 --> 00:16:13,639
Aren't you at the consortium?

323
00:16:14,573 --> 00:16:15,708
I finished up and came back.

324
00:16:16,075 --> 00:16:17,543
I wanted to check the comprehensive ICU patients

325
00:16:17,943 --> 00:16:19,878
and came to see you because I was worried.

326
00:16:21,080 --> 00:16:22,448
What's there to worry about?

327
00:16:23,649 --> 00:16:24,717
Everyone in the group chat

328
00:16:24,717 --> 00:16:25,884
is talking about the center director position.

329
00:16:27,286 --> 00:16:28,587
What do you think?

330
00:16:29,521 --> 00:16:30,322
What can I think?

331
00:16:30,856 --> 00:16:31,824
It came out of nowhere.

332
00:16:32,358 --> 00:16:33,892
It really caught me off guard.

333
00:16:35,227 --> 00:16:36,628
It is a little strange.

334
00:16:37,596 --> 00:16:39,164
There wasn't a single hint beforehand.

335
00:16:39,531 --> 00:16:40,666
Then suddenly they announced an appointment.

336
00:16:43,469 --> 00:16:44,837
Still, such an arrangement

337
00:16:45,904 --> 00:16:47,039
wasn't entirely unforeseeable.

338
00:16:48,207 --> 00:16:48,774
President Wang.

339
00:16:49,375 --> 00:16:50,909
I've always believed this surgery

340
00:16:51,076 --> 00:16:52,010
was more suitable for Lin Yi to lead

341
00:16:52,010 --> 00:16:53,012
than Director Sheng.

342
00:16:53,679 --> 00:16:54,313
And yesterday,

343
00:16:54,313 --> 00:16:55,814
the patient's condition suddenly worsened.

344
00:16:55,914 --> 00:16:57,116
Then why didn't you tell me?

345
00:16:58,150 --> 00:16:59,385
I was at the hospital yesterday.

346
00:17:00,152 --> 00:17:00,686
Did you think

347
00:17:00,686 --> 00:17:01,553
I wouldn't support you?

348
00:17:03,789 --> 00:17:04,256
Xiaofeng.

349
00:17:05,591 --> 00:17:06,592
I trust you.

350
00:17:07,393 --> 00:17:08,427
Do you trust me?

351
00:17:10,929 --> 00:17:12,131
If you continue being

352
00:17:12,131 --> 00:17:12,998
someone with no sense of limits,

353
00:17:13,766 --> 00:17:15,134
then the hospital really must consider

354
00:17:16,168 --> 00:17:17,069
whether it can still

355
00:17:17,069 --> 00:17:17,836
entrust you with major responsibility.

356
00:17:20,305 --> 00:17:21,006
So,

357
00:17:21,974 --> 00:17:23,108
the price was bound to come.

358
00:17:25,010 --> 00:17:26,078
With Du Yan's surgery,

359
00:17:26,879 --> 00:17:27,846
I acted first and reported afterward.

360
00:17:29,515 --> 00:17:30,716
That must have put the hospital leadership in a difficult position.

361
00:17:32,985 --> 00:17:34,253
So you mean

362
00:17:35,087 --> 00:17:37,089
the Heart Center director position

363
00:17:37,990 --> 00:17:39,558
is definitely Director Sheng's?

364
00:17:39,725 --> 00:17:40,626
I don't have enough seniority.

365
00:17:42,227 --> 00:17:43,228
This so-called selection

366
00:17:44,129 --> 00:17:45,631
is probably just a formality.

367
00:17:48,667 --> 00:17:49,735
Whether I get it

368
00:17:50,235 --> 00:17:50,803
isn't important.

369
00:17:52,171 --> 00:17:52,905
What's important is

370
00:17:53,572 --> 00:17:54,606
if Sheng Nian really

371
00:17:54,673 --> 00:17:56,175
becomes Heart Center director,

372
00:17:56,842 --> 00:17:57,943
he'll directly control

373
00:17:58,010 --> 00:17:59,278
Cardiology's personnel appointments

374
00:17:59,311 --> 00:18:00,345
and performance distribution.

375
00:18:01,013 --> 00:18:02,214
Then Cardiology and Cardiac Surgery

376
00:18:02,247 --> 00:18:03,649
will no longer be able to cooperate.

377
00:18:04,416 --> 00:18:06,552
The Heart Center will exist in name only.

378
00:18:06,885 --> 00:18:08,153
He doesn't believe in cooperation.

379
00:18:09,188 --> 00:18:10,022
He only believes in swallowing us whole.

380
00:18:11,957 --> 00:18:12,925
Joint clinics,

381
00:18:12,958 --> 00:18:13,692
hybrid procedures—

382
00:18:13,826 --> 00:18:14,693
forget all of it.

383
00:18:15,360 --> 00:18:16,929
He may also stop sending people

384
00:18:16,929 --> 00:18:17,996
to support Guizhou.

385
00:18:20,466 --> 00:18:21,567
More importantly,

386
00:18:22,201 --> 00:18:23,569
I'm afraid what happened with Du Yan

387
00:18:24,703 --> 00:18:26,038
won't be an isolated case.

388
00:18:32,311 --> 00:18:32,945
So,

389
00:18:33,412 --> 00:18:34,213
no matter what,

390
00:18:35,147 --> 00:18:36,348
I have to step up.

391
00:18:37,149 --> 00:18:38,317
I can't surrender without a fight.

392
00:18:38,884 --> 00:18:39,985
I have to face it positively.

393
00:18:40,652 --> 00:18:40,986
Brother,

394
00:18:41,687 --> 00:18:42,488
I support you.

395
00:18:44,389 --> 00:18:45,824
Start by eating properly.

396
00:18:47,526 --> 00:18:48,393
I'll get back to work.

397
00:18:48,894 --> 00:18:50,028
Why are you still here so late?

398
00:18:50,696 --> 00:18:51,230
There's still work

399
00:18:51,230 --> 00:18:51,830
in the comprehensive ICU.

400
00:18:51,997 --> 00:18:53,265
I'm going back to the consortium tomorrow.

401
00:18:53,665 --> 00:18:54,166
All right.

402
00:18:54,266 --> 00:18:54,666
Okay.

403
00:19:04,209 --> 00:19:05,077
Starting next week,

404
00:19:05,410 --> 00:19:07,045
we'll make some adjustments

405
00:19:07,446 --> 00:19:08,413
to outpatient, inpatient, and surgical scheduling.

406
00:19:09,314 --> 00:19:10,649
The notice was already

407
00:19:11,049 --> 00:19:12,084
emailed to everyone before the meeting.

408
00:19:16,788 --> 00:19:17,556
Considering the hospital

409
00:19:17,656 --> 00:19:19,024
is surrounded by many commercial districts,

410
00:19:19,358 --> 00:19:20,893
office workers have no time during the day

411
00:19:21,160 --> 00:19:22,561
and can only seek care at night.

412
00:19:23,095 --> 00:19:24,229
So starting next week,

413
00:19:24,730 --> 00:19:25,564
I plan to add

414
00:19:25,631 --> 00:19:26,965
weekend evening clinics,

415
00:19:27,165 --> 00:19:28,166
including specialist clinics,

416
00:19:28,667 --> 00:19:29,968
to meet patient demand.

417
00:19:35,274 --> 00:19:36,708
But on weekends and evenings,

418
00:19:36,808 --> 00:19:37,943
lab tests and imaging

419
00:19:38,544 --> 00:19:39,411
won't be available in time.

420
00:19:39,878 --> 00:19:40,712
I'll solve that.

421
00:19:43,515 --> 00:19:44,016
Next,

422
00:19:44,349 --> 00:19:45,784
I want to emphasize again

423
00:19:46,151 --> 00:19:47,052
service with a smile.

424
00:19:47,719 --> 00:19:48,954
People are emotional beings.

425
00:19:49,555 --> 00:19:50,489
Our attitude

426
00:19:50,522 --> 00:19:51,356
directly affects

427
00:19:51,356 --> 00:19:52,558
the patient's care experience

428
00:19:52,958 --> 00:19:54,092
and their trust in our department

429
00:19:54,326 --> 00:19:55,294
and in the hospital.

430
00:19:56,895 --> 00:19:57,829
If we want to retain patients

431
00:19:58,564 --> 00:19:59,665
and attract more,

432
00:20:00,032 --> 00:20:00,832
we need to provide

433
00:20:00,866 --> 00:20:01,800
the best service possible.

434
00:20:04,303 --> 00:20:04,870
Also,

435
00:20:05,237 --> 00:20:06,204
starting this month,

436
00:20:06,705 --> 00:20:08,040
we'll implement a bottom-ranking elimination system.

437
00:20:08,607 --> 00:20:09,975
Each month, the group

438
00:20:09,975 --> 00:20:10,509
with the worst performance

439
00:20:10,709 --> 00:20:12,644
will have its team leader return to front-line shifts

440
00:20:13,078 --> 00:20:14,046
and lead by example.

441
00:20:18,884 --> 00:20:19,318
Finally,

442
00:20:19,651 --> 00:20:20,652
while I hope everyone gives

443
00:20:20,652 --> 00:20:21,720
their best performance,

444
00:20:22,187 --> 00:20:23,388
research must not be neglected.

445
00:20:23,956 --> 00:20:24,823
Anyone here

446
00:20:25,023 --> 00:20:25,424
who has no publication

447
00:20:25,490 --> 00:20:26,758
this year

448
00:20:27,025 --> 00:20:27,960
will have the weighting of their bonus

449
00:20:28,393 --> 00:20:29,595
reduced by 20 percent.

450
00:20:36,468 --> 00:20:37,436
Other

451
00:20:37,569 --> 00:20:38,837
implementation-related

452
00:20:38,971 --> 00:20:39,671
details and adjustments

453
00:20:40,239 --> 00:20:41,506
are listed in the notice.

454
00:20:41,873 --> 00:20:43,542
Please read it carefully

455
00:20:43,976 --> 00:20:44,743
and follow it strictly.

456
00:20:57,489 --> 00:20:58,023
I know

457
00:20:58,924 --> 00:21:00,425
some of you have objections

458
00:21:00,993 --> 00:21:01,827
to this round of reforms.

459
00:21:02,728 --> 00:21:03,962
But I hope you'll understand.

460
00:21:05,397 --> 00:21:06,365
You all know

461
00:21:06,999 --> 00:21:08,367
the competition for Heart Center director

462
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:09,201
has begun.

463
00:21:10,669 --> 00:21:11,436
Over the next few months,

464
00:21:12,037 --> 00:21:13,205
I plan to give it everything I have.

465
00:21:15,574 --> 00:21:17,209
I also ask you to trust me one more time

466
00:21:18,110 --> 00:21:18,844
and join me

467
00:21:19,911 --> 00:21:20,646
in this all-or-nothing battle.

468
00:21:36,828 --> 00:21:37,629
I sent the video

469
00:21:37,696 --> 00:21:38,463
of your surgery on Du Yan

470
00:21:38,530 --> 00:21:39,464
at the first opportunity

471
00:21:39,564 --> 00:21:40,632
to President Chen in Qinghai.

472
00:21:41,333 --> 00:21:42,968
He was thrilled after seeing it

473
00:21:43,435 --> 00:21:44,269
and wants to invite you

474
00:21:44,436 --> 00:21:45,437
to establish

475
00:21:45,604 --> 00:21:46,438
an expert workstation there.

476
00:21:46,838 --> 00:21:48,106
That's wonderful. I'm willing to go.

477
00:21:48,840 --> 00:21:50,075
They have a large patient base

478
00:21:50,275 --> 00:21:51,309
but lack talent,

479
00:21:51,610 --> 00:21:52,878
especially specialists capable

480
00:21:52,878 --> 00:21:53,812
of performing TAVR.

481
00:21:57,416 --> 00:21:57,849
Director Sheng,

482
00:21:59,785 --> 00:22:00,352
in any case,

483
00:22:01,086 --> 00:22:01,920
the responsibility

484
00:22:01,987 --> 00:22:02,921
of expanding Dongli Cardiac Surgery

485
00:22:02,921 --> 00:22:03,555
is now yours.

486
00:22:04,089 --> 00:22:05,524
Build up our technology and reputation

487
00:22:05,691 --> 00:22:06,325
there.

488
00:22:07,025 --> 00:22:07,626
Are you confident?

489
00:22:08,393 --> 00:22:08,727
Yes.

490
00:22:31,283 --> 00:22:32,484
Congratulations, Director Sheng.

491
00:22:33,085 --> 00:22:33,885
I told you,

492
00:22:35,053 --> 00:22:36,755
the Heart Center director position

493
00:22:37,089 --> 00:22:38,623
being opened at this time

494
00:22:39,191 --> 00:22:39,791
basically means

495
00:22:40,192 --> 00:22:41,893
it's already yours.

496
00:22:43,161 --> 00:22:44,529
It's too early to say that.

497
00:22:45,430 --> 00:22:46,365
We still need to keep a low profile.

498
00:22:47,265 --> 00:22:47,933
Of course, of course.

499
00:22:49,334 --> 00:22:50,335
We're among our own people.

500
00:22:50,435 --> 00:22:51,203
I'm only saying it privately.

501
00:22:51,503 --> 00:22:52,504
Anyway, I believe

502
00:22:52,604 --> 00:22:54,172
you truly deserve it.

503
00:22:54,439 --> 00:22:56,274
I hope you'll

504
00:22:56,608 --> 00:22:57,409
look after me in the future.

505
00:22:59,711 --> 00:23:01,046
You've always been reliable.

506
00:23:01,246 --> 00:23:02,748
That paper of mine last time

507
00:23:03,248 --> 00:23:03,849
was all thanks to you.

508
00:23:04,750 --> 00:23:05,283
It was nothing.

509
00:23:05,884 --> 00:23:07,719
It's my honor to do my small part

510
00:23:07,853 --> 00:23:09,321
for you, Director Sheng.

511
00:23:12,891 --> 00:23:13,358
Director,

512
00:23:13,558 --> 00:23:14,559
I have

513
00:23:14,893 --> 00:23:16,194
a batch of bioprosthetic valves

514
00:23:17,129 --> 00:23:18,196
that are still within date,

515
00:23:18,964 --> 00:23:20,065
but are about to expire.

516
00:23:20,866 --> 00:23:22,634
I'd like your help using some of them.

517
00:23:24,102 --> 00:23:25,170
Well,

518
00:23:26,438 --> 00:23:27,572
we'd need patients

519
00:23:27,639 --> 00:23:29,074
who actually meet indications for valve replacement.

520
00:23:30,876 --> 00:23:32,411
The main issue is the manufacturer...

521
00:23:32,611 --> 00:23:34,679
The return policy is extremely strict.

522
00:23:35,280 --> 00:23:36,481
I have a lot sitting in inventory.

523
00:23:37,349 --> 00:23:38,550
The losses would be significant.

524
00:23:39,851 --> 00:23:40,685
Director, don't worry.

525
00:23:41,386 --> 00:23:42,354
Your rebate percentage—

526
00:23:42,387 --> 00:23:43,088
Enough. Stop.

527
00:23:46,892 --> 00:23:47,559
I'll see what I can do.

528
00:23:52,964 --> 00:23:53,398
Director.

529
00:23:53,799 --> 00:23:54,833
Neurology has a patient

530
00:23:54,833 --> 00:23:55,634
they want us to evaluate.

531
00:23:55,967 --> 00:23:56,468
What's the situation?

532
00:23:57,002 --> 00:23:57,836
She came through the ER.

533
00:23:57,936 --> 00:23:59,037
It was originally a stroke

534
00:23:59,070 --> 00:24:00,038
affecting the visual cortex,

535
00:24:00,105 --> 00:24:00,972
causing visual field loss.

536
00:24:01,406 --> 00:24:02,207
They already gave

537
00:24:02,207 --> 00:24:03,308
timely thrombolytic treatment.

538
00:24:04,009 --> 00:24:05,510
But during the admission workup,

539
00:24:05,544 --> 00:24:06,945
they found atrial fibrillation

540
00:24:07,112 --> 00:24:08,113
with a left atrial thrombus.

541
00:24:08,847 --> 00:24:09,681
Then her stroke

542
00:24:10,048 --> 00:24:11,349
was very likely caused by the AF.

543
00:24:11,850 --> 00:24:12,651
Most likely.

544
00:24:12,984 --> 00:24:13,885
Two years ago,

545
00:24:13,885 --> 00:24:14,920
she had mitral valve repair

546
00:24:14,953 --> 00:24:16,488
in our Cardiac Surgery department.

547
00:24:16,988 --> 00:24:18,290
I think Director Lin did it.

548
00:24:18,924 --> 00:24:19,624
What's her name?

549
00:24:19,825 --> 00:24:21,092
A pretty unusual one.

550
00:24:21,326 --> 00:24:22,727
Her surname is Mu. Mu Qiangwei.

551
00:24:34,272 --> 00:24:34,840
Qiangwei?

552
00:24:37,409 --> 00:24:38,510
Director Xiaofeng.

553
00:24:40,078 --> 00:24:41,079
Long time no see.

554
00:24:42,848 --> 00:24:43,648
Long time no see.

555
00:24:44,583 --> 00:24:46,117
Why did you lie to me?

556
00:24:47,385 --> 00:24:48,553
You're all liars.

557
00:24:48,720 --> 00:24:49,588
You're all liars.

558
00:24:49,721 --> 00:24:50,522
Stay away from me.

559
00:24:53,225 --> 00:24:54,526
Actually, deep down,

560
00:24:54,559 --> 00:24:55,627
I know you're good people.

561
00:24:57,262 --> 00:24:58,029
People like me,

562
00:24:58,363 --> 00:24:59,197
Aunt Yang,

563
00:24:59,764 --> 00:25:00,265
and Hua'er—

564
00:25:01,766 --> 00:25:03,668
we're like duckweed and wild grass.

565
00:25:03,969 --> 00:25:05,036
No one cares about us.

566
00:25:05,704 --> 00:25:06,571
Only you

567
00:25:07,806 --> 00:25:08,773
treated us like we mattered.

568
00:25:09,407 --> 00:25:09,975
Thank you.

569
00:25:14,813 --> 00:25:15,614
Sit down.

570
00:25:18,316 --> 00:25:18,984
How are you?

571
00:25:21,453 --> 00:25:22,654
Sometimes

572
00:25:22,687 --> 00:25:23,755
I still get a little dizzy.

573
00:25:25,757 --> 00:25:26,691
What about your vision?

574
00:25:27,559 --> 00:25:29,628
I can see clearly in the center,

575
00:25:30,428 --> 00:25:32,564
but the sides are still blurry.

576
00:25:35,867 --> 00:25:37,469
Did you attend follow-ups on time?

577
00:25:38,003 --> 00:25:39,237
Otherwise it wouldn't have become this serious.

578
00:25:40,071 --> 00:25:40,839
I did.

579
00:25:40,872 --> 00:25:42,073
I only missed the last one.

580
00:25:43,909 --> 00:25:45,143
I tried to make it up a few days later,

581
00:25:45,677 --> 00:25:46,811
but security stopped me.

582
00:25:47,412 --> 00:25:49,080
I couldn't get an extra appointment with Director Lin.

583
00:26:03,628 --> 00:26:05,864
Later I also tried to see you

584
00:26:05,964 --> 00:26:06,464
in the special clinic,

585
00:26:07,732 --> 00:26:09,267
but you were busy that day too.

586
00:26:10,168 --> 00:26:10,869
Director Zhou! Director Zhou!

587
00:26:10,869 --> 00:26:11,569
Sorry, there's an emergency.

588
00:26:11,569 --> 00:26:12,270
Everyone, please make way.

589
00:26:12,404 --> 00:26:12,804
Don't worry.

590
00:26:12,804 --> 00:26:13,271
Please wait a moment.

591
00:26:13,405 --> 00:26:13,705
Just a moment.

592
00:26:13,705 --> 00:26:14,673
Please move aside.

593
00:26:15,440 --> 00:26:16,308
There's a patient on the ward

594
00:26:16,308 --> 00:26:17,042
with a special situation.

595
00:26:17,175 --> 00:26:18,243
The director has to handle it first.

596
00:26:18,243 --> 00:26:19,344
Please wait here, all right?

597
00:26:19,544 --> 00:26:20,745
So I didn't bother you.

598
00:26:21,012 --> 00:26:22,314
You should've messaged me.

599
00:26:23,114 --> 00:26:24,416
I thought I'd just

600
00:26:25,083 --> 00:26:26,151
go back to the clinic later.

601
00:26:26,952 --> 00:26:28,186
Who knew I'd end up in the ER?

602
00:26:44,369 --> 00:26:44,936
I'm sorry.

603
00:26:45,604 --> 00:26:46,571
This was our failure.

604
00:26:47,072 --> 00:26:47,973
No,

605
00:26:49,641 --> 00:26:51,009
it wasn't your fault.

606
00:26:54,045 --> 00:26:55,046
I spoke with your attending physician

607
00:26:55,046 --> 00:26:55,747
and discussed your condition.

608
00:26:56,247 --> 00:26:57,682
The immediate stroke crisis

609
00:26:57,782 --> 00:26:58,650
has passed.

610
00:26:59,084 --> 00:27:00,151
But you still need

611
00:27:00,151 --> 00:27:00,919
continued anticoagulation.

612
00:27:02,053 --> 00:27:03,521
Once the thrombus is gone,

613
00:27:03,788 --> 00:27:04,589
we'll address

614
00:27:04,589 --> 00:27:05,557
the atrial fibrillation.

615
00:27:06,625 --> 00:27:07,625
Director Xiaofeng,

616
00:27:08,793 --> 00:27:10,328
with you here, I feel safe.

617
00:27:12,664 --> 00:27:13,798
Xiao Ye, arrange

618
00:27:14,065 --> 00:27:14,466
to transfer her

619
00:27:14,532 --> 00:27:15,367
to our department later.

620
00:27:15,600 --> 00:27:16,034
Okay.

621
00:27:16,935 --> 00:27:17,602
Really?

622
00:27:18,703 --> 00:27:19,637
That's wonderful.

623
00:27:20,905 --> 00:27:22,107
Qiangwei is an old friend

624
00:27:22,173 --> 00:27:22,874
of our Heart Center.

625
00:27:23,108 --> 00:27:23,975
Take good care of her.

626
00:27:24,709 --> 00:27:25,110
Okay.

627
00:27:31,683 --> 00:27:33,385
Make way, please.

628
00:27:33,885 --> 00:27:34,753
Make way. Thank you.

629
00:27:34,753 --> 00:27:35,920
Thank you.

630
00:27:36,254 --> 00:27:36,855
She looks so familiar, Sister Yalan.

631
00:27:38,690 --> 00:27:40,158
Right?

632
00:27:40,625 --> 00:27:41,159
Dr. Liu.

633
00:27:51,703 --> 00:27:52,303
You...

634
00:28:01,913 --> 00:28:02,547
Qiangwei.

635
00:28:03,248 --> 00:28:03,848
Qiangwei.

636
00:28:04,916 --> 00:28:05,683
What happened to you?

637
00:28:06,751 --> 00:28:07,719
It's nothing. Just a minor problem.

638
00:28:08,186 --> 00:28:09,120
Director Zhou admitted me.

639
00:28:10,155 --> 00:28:11,189
All right.

640
00:28:12,123 --> 00:28:12,524
If you need anything,

641
00:28:12,691 --> 00:28:13,425
come find us in the office.

642
00:28:13,425 --> 00:28:13,992
You'd better not need anything.

643
00:28:14,959 --> 00:28:15,760
Go ahead with your work.

644
00:28:16,094 --> 00:28:16,895
Director Xiaofeng.

645
00:28:21,966 --> 00:28:23,034
Why are you here?

646
00:28:23,234 --> 00:28:24,069
Waiting for you.

647
00:28:24,669 --> 00:28:25,270
Qiangwei,

648
00:28:29,407 --> 00:28:29,841
I'll help prepare

649
00:28:30,308 --> 00:28:31,176
the things you need

650
00:28:31,242 --> 00:28:32,243
for your stay.

651
00:28:32,310 --> 00:28:33,211
You talk with the director first.

652
00:28:33,445 --> 00:28:34,646
Okay. Thank you, Sister Yalan.

653
00:28:35,880 --> 00:28:36,247
All right.

654
00:28:43,922 --> 00:28:44,956
Pretty good.

655
00:28:45,790 --> 00:28:46,825
Especially just now,

656
00:28:47,358 --> 00:28:49,094
coming out of the elevator

657
00:28:50,295 --> 00:28:51,763
and seeing this familiar place

658
00:28:52,564 --> 00:28:53,631
and familiar faces—

659
00:28:53,965 --> 00:28:54,632
it felt comforting.

660
00:28:55,567 --> 00:28:56,034
Qiangwei.

661
00:28:58,603 --> 00:28:59,170
Director Lin.

662
00:28:59,871 --> 00:29:00,505
You're here too.

663
00:29:00,772 --> 00:29:01,573
Why are you hospitalized?

664
00:29:02,207 --> 00:29:03,308
I came to the ER

665
00:29:03,975 --> 00:29:04,676
a couple of days ago.

666
00:29:05,076 --> 00:29:05,543
A stroke.

667
00:29:06,878 --> 00:29:08,446
Neurology gave me thrombolysis.

668
00:29:09,114 --> 00:29:10,315
They also found atrial fibrillation

669
00:29:10,648 --> 00:29:11,716
with a left atrial thrombus.

670
00:29:14,853 --> 00:29:15,520
What about now?

671
00:29:16,454 --> 00:29:17,188
The stroke was most likely

672
00:29:17,255 --> 00:29:18,289
caused by the AF.

673
00:29:18,923 --> 00:29:20,024
Because follow-up wasn't timely,

674
00:29:20,492 --> 00:29:22,127
her optic nerve is now damaged

675
00:29:22,961 --> 00:29:23,962
and her visual field is restricted.

676
00:29:27,932 --> 00:29:29,167
You should have come for follow-up last month.

677
00:29:29,200 --> 00:29:30,068
Why didn't you?

678
00:29:30,602 --> 00:29:31,402
I did.

679
00:29:32,203 --> 00:29:33,505
Hello, I'm here to see Director Lin.

680
00:29:33,571 --> 00:29:34,239
Have you checked in?

681
00:29:34,639 --> 00:29:35,507
I'm here for follow-up.

682
00:29:35,707 --> 00:29:36,441
You don't have an appointment?

683
00:29:36,841 --> 00:29:37,876
Director Lin doesn't add extra patients.

684
00:29:38,710 --> 00:29:39,210
Director Sheng

685
00:29:39,244 --> 00:29:40,078
has repeatedly emphasized lately

686
00:29:40,211 --> 00:29:41,279
that Director Lin works hard in surgery,

687
00:29:41,312 --> 00:29:42,046
so his clinic volume is limited

688
00:29:42,247 --> 00:29:43,248
and no one may be let in without an appointment.

689
00:29:44,582 --> 00:29:45,350
I understand.

690
00:29:45,583 --> 00:29:46,718
But I'm a former patient of his.

691
00:29:46,951 --> 00:29:48,319
Something came up at last week's follow-up.

692
00:29:48,553 --> 00:29:50,088
I couldn't get an appointment today.

693
00:29:50,255 --> 00:29:51,389
Could you ask him for me?

694
00:29:51,689 --> 00:29:52,323
My name is Qiangwei.

695
00:29:52,357 --> 00:29:53,224
He'll know who I am.

696
00:29:53,391 --> 00:29:54,159
It's not that I don't want to help.

697
00:29:54,559 --> 00:29:55,393
If I let you in,

698
00:29:55,393 --> 00:29:56,394
I could lose my job.

699
00:29:56,995 --> 00:29:57,362
But...

700
00:29:57,428 --> 00:29:58,396
Please don't make things difficult for me.

701
00:30:05,003 --> 00:30:05,837
Why didn't you

702
00:30:05,837 --> 00:30:06,471
tell security?

703
00:30:10,642 --> 00:30:11,643
Tell security what?

704
00:30:12,277 --> 00:30:13,244
Do I manage security?

705
00:30:13,645 --> 00:30:14,679
The guards outside your clinic

706
00:30:14,679 --> 00:30:15,480
don't report to you?

707
00:30:15,747 --> 00:30:17,448
Is it that hard to make an exception for a returning patient?

708
00:30:17,682 --> 00:30:18,950
I'm a doctor. I manage patients.

709
00:30:18,983 --> 00:30:19,784
Security is managed by you.

710
00:30:19,784 --> 00:30:20,785
It's managed by hospital administration.

711
00:30:20,885 --> 00:30:22,053
Then manage your patients properly.

712
00:30:22,387 --> 00:30:23,121
Before I went to Guizhou,

713
00:30:23,154 --> 00:30:24,122
I entrusted Qiangwei to you.

714
00:30:24,656 --> 00:30:25,690
Is this how responsible you've been?

715
00:30:26,191 --> 00:30:27,091
She missed a follow-up,

716
00:30:27,125 --> 00:30:27,892
and you didn't even know.

717
00:30:32,864 --> 00:30:34,232
You two are exactly the same as before.

718
00:30:34,666 --> 00:30:35,333
Whenever it's about a patient,

719
00:30:35,366 --> 00:30:36,401
you start bickering.

720
00:30:36,935 --> 00:30:37,602
Nothing has changed.

721
00:30:44,475 --> 00:30:45,910
I'm fine, aren't I?

722
00:30:48,713 --> 00:30:49,447
Get some rest.

723
00:30:49,847 --> 00:30:50,481
I'll come see you again.

724
00:30:52,383 --> 00:30:53,484
Okay, Director Xiaofeng.

725
00:30:56,287 --> 00:30:57,555
Director Xiaofeng, he...

726
00:30:57,555 --> 00:30:58,089
Ignore him.

727
00:30:58,389 --> 00:30:59,290
That's what happens when someone becomes a leader.

728
00:31:01,826 --> 00:31:02,727
Since you're admitted,

729
00:31:03,895 --> 00:31:04,696
just stay and rest.

730
00:31:07,265 --> 00:31:07,966
Are you still alone?

731
00:31:08,566 --> 00:31:10,001
Yes. Still alone.

732
00:31:10,835 --> 00:31:12,704
Then who will look after you this time?

733
00:31:13,571 --> 00:31:15,039
I can take care of myself.

734
00:31:17,709 --> 00:31:18,076
By the way,

735
00:31:18,409 --> 00:31:19,477
I opened a nail salon.

736
00:31:20,879 --> 00:31:21,846
A nail salon?

737
00:31:22,113 --> 00:31:22,480
Yes.

738
00:31:26,718 --> 00:31:27,085
Here.

739
00:31:27,252 --> 00:31:28,319
These are trial vouchers from our shop.

740
00:31:29,687 --> 00:31:29,954
Take them.

741
00:31:30,455 --> 00:31:31,155
Come by sometime.

742
00:31:31,489 --> 00:31:32,423
I'll do your nails.

743
00:31:32,624 --> 00:31:33,758
What would I do with these?

744
00:31:33,791 --> 00:31:34,726
I wear gloves every day.

745
00:31:34,759 --> 00:31:35,593
I don't get manicures.

746
00:31:36,327 --> 00:31:37,762
Then please say hello to Dr. Xiaoran for me too.

747
00:31:39,964 --> 00:31:40,865
Give her my regards.

748
00:31:44,168 --> 00:31:45,169
Just take them.

749
00:31:51,175 --> 00:31:52,076
One is enough for me.

750
00:31:52,610 --> 00:31:53,511
Take them all.

751
00:31:53,511 --> 00:31:54,512
No, that'd be wasteful.

752
00:31:54,512 --> 00:31:55,079
Keep the rest.

753
00:31:57,215 --> 00:31:57,548
All right.

754
00:31:57,849 --> 00:31:59,384
Come back for more if you run out.

755
00:32:02,153 --> 00:32:03,087
Fine. Get some rest.

756
00:32:03,187 --> 00:32:03,655
I'm leaving.

757
00:32:03,955 --> 00:32:05,690
Okay. Thank you, Director Lin.

758
00:32:32,116 --> 00:32:32,717
Qiangwei.

759
00:32:35,553 --> 00:32:36,554
Dr. Xiaoran.

760
00:32:37,588 --> 00:32:38,790
My brother said you were hospitalized.

761
00:32:39,157 --> 00:32:39,958
How are you?

762
00:32:40,158 --> 00:32:40,792
I'm fine.

763
00:32:40,992 --> 00:32:41,759
Moving here

764
00:32:41,926 --> 00:32:43,227
made me feel much safer.

765
00:32:43,494 --> 00:32:44,529
I read your chart.

766
00:32:44,562 --> 00:32:45,363
There's no major problem.

767
00:32:45,863 --> 00:32:46,764
Don't worry.

768
00:32:48,232 --> 00:32:49,167
Is this your room?

769
00:32:49,767 --> 00:32:50,068
Let's go.

770
00:32:50,168 --> 00:32:50,568
Okay.

771
00:32:52,003 --> 00:32:52,603
My brother said

772
00:32:52,603 --> 00:32:53,705
you opened a nail salon.

773
00:32:54,172 --> 00:32:55,039
How's business?

774
00:32:55,373 --> 00:32:56,240
It's just a small shop.

775
00:32:56,307 --> 00:32:57,308
Business is okay.

776
00:32:57,608 --> 00:32:58,409
At least

777
00:32:58,810 --> 00:33:00,545
it covers rent and food.

778
00:33:01,913 --> 00:33:02,647
Here, lie down.

779
00:33:02,814 --> 00:33:03,114
Okay.

780
00:33:04,315 --> 00:33:05,683
And the shop...

781
00:33:05,983 --> 00:33:07,151
is very close to Jianbo's home.

782
00:33:07,685 --> 00:33:08,987
I can also visit his parents.

783
00:33:10,054 --> 00:33:10,722
That's wonderful.

784
00:33:12,724 --> 00:33:13,524
What about you, Dr. Xiaoran?

785
00:33:13,558 --> 00:33:14,125
How are you?

786
00:33:15,193 --> 00:33:16,794
Me? About the same.

787
00:33:17,929 --> 00:33:19,230
Eating, sleeping, working.

788
00:33:19,797 --> 00:33:20,631
Seeing all of you this time

789
00:33:20,665 --> 00:33:21,866
feels so familiar,

790
00:33:22,367 --> 00:33:23,334
but also different.

791
00:33:23,601 --> 00:33:25,169
Your hair has grown so much.

792
00:33:25,303 --> 00:33:26,237
Yes. I haven't cut it.

793
00:33:27,872 --> 00:33:29,474
And Director Xiaofeng

794
00:33:29,841 --> 00:33:30,808
became department director.

795
00:33:31,175 --> 00:33:31,876
Director Lin

796
00:33:32,143 --> 00:33:33,211
became such a famous expert

797
00:33:33,244 --> 00:33:33,878
that no one can get an appointment.

798
00:33:34,345 --> 00:33:35,213
And you, Dr. Xiaoran,

799
00:33:35,847 --> 00:33:36,547
are so busy too,

800
00:33:36,614 --> 00:33:37,515
always rushing around.

801
00:33:38,716 --> 00:33:40,084
You all seem more impressive now.

802
00:33:41,586 --> 00:33:41,986
Yes.

803
00:33:42,153 --> 00:33:43,488
Everyone is busier than before.

804
00:33:45,990 --> 00:33:48,993
Are Director Xiaofeng and Director Lin

805
00:33:49,594 --> 00:33:51,028
having some disagreement?

806
00:34:00,972 --> 00:34:02,640
And you and Director Lin—

807
00:34:03,441 --> 00:34:04,375
are you two okay?

808
00:34:08,079 --> 00:34:09,013
We separated.

809
00:34:11,349 --> 00:34:12,183
It's fine.

810
00:34:13,084 --> 00:34:13,951
It was an amicable breakup.

811
00:34:14,452 --> 00:34:15,753
When I saw Director Lin today,

812
00:34:15,787 --> 00:34:16,888
he did seem a little strange.

813
00:34:17,522 --> 00:34:18,689
What a shame.

814
00:34:18,923 --> 00:34:20,124
You're both such good people.

815
00:34:22,794 --> 00:34:24,996
So much has happened in two years.

816
00:34:28,733 --> 00:34:29,834
Two years

817
00:34:30,435 --> 00:34:31,402
went by in a flash.

818
00:34:32,870 --> 00:34:33,438
But seeing you

819
00:34:33,438 --> 00:34:34,372
still feels warm and familiar.

820
00:34:36,007 --> 00:34:36,774
Give me your hand.

821
00:34:37,475 --> 00:34:38,042
Let me see.

822
00:34:40,144 --> 00:34:41,045
Come to my shop sometime.

823
00:34:41,079 --> 00:34:41,946
I'll do your nails.

824
00:34:42,847 --> 00:34:43,714
I don't have time.

825
00:34:43,815 --> 00:34:44,348
And

826
00:34:45,049 --> 00:34:46,117
it's inconvenient for work.

827
00:34:46,451 --> 00:34:47,685
It can just be nail care.

828
00:34:47,852 --> 00:34:48,152
All right.

829
00:34:56,594 --> 00:34:57,728
Hello, Qianqian's mom.

830
00:34:58,162 --> 00:34:58,830
Senlin's mom.

831
00:34:58,996 --> 00:34:59,964
Do you have time right now?

832
00:35:00,398 --> 00:35:01,165
Yes. Go ahead.

833
00:35:01,532 --> 00:35:01,999
Here's the thing.

834
00:35:02,366 --> 00:35:03,167
Our Qianqian

835
00:35:03,167 --> 00:35:04,836
had surgery at Dongli last time.

836
00:35:05,169 --> 00:35:06,070
Would you mind

837
00:35:06,204 --> 00:35:07,572
looking at his medical records for me?

838
00:35:08,005 --> 00:35:08,473
What's wrong?

839
00:35:09,040 --> 00:35:09,807
Nothing major.

840
00:35:10,108 --> 00:35:11,609
The surgery went smoothly.

841
00:35:12,110 --> 00:35:12,810
But

842
00:35:13,010 --> 00:35:14,278
when we returned home

843
00:35:14,312 --> 00:35:15,546
for follow-up at our local hospital,

844
00:35:16,080 --> 00:35:17,448
the director there said

845
00:35:18,182 --> 00:35:19,550
that a child like Qianqian

846
00:35:19,650 --> 00:35:21,319
might not have needed open-heart surgery.

847
00:35:22,286 --> 00:35:23,187
Who performed it?

848
00:35:24,489 --> 00:35:26,190
Director Sheng Nian from Cardiac Surgery.

849
00:35:26,557 --> 00:35:27,692
I was afraid you were too busy,

850
00:35:27,792 --> 00:35:28,693
so I didn't bother you.

851
00:35:29,627 --> 00:35:30,495
As for Director Sheng,

852
00:35:30,628 --> 00:35:31,395
I told him

853
00:35:31,496 --> 00:35:32,463
that we're friends of yours.

854
00:35:33,030 --> 00:35:34,332
He was very polite too.

855
00:35:35,066 --> 00:35:36,167
But now

856
00:35:36,601 --> 00:35:38,236
I don't know who to believe.

857
00:35:38,636 --> 00:35:39,804
I just can't

858
00:35:40,171 --> 00:35:41,606
put my mind at ease.

859
00:35:43,107 --> 00:35:44,075
Send me the records.

860
00:35:44,842 --> 00:35:46,477
I'll review them and get back to you.

861
00:35:46,511 --> 00:35:47,612
Thank you. Thank you.

862
00:35:47,612 --> 00:35:47,945
Okay.

863
00:36:01,759 --> 00:36:03,127
That was Qianqian's mom

864
00:36:03,161 --> 00:36:04,162
from the patient support group.

865
00:36:04,428 --> 00:36:05,630
I've thought it over,

866
00:36:05,863 --> 00:36:06,531
and I still think

867
00:36:06,664 --> 00:36:07,532
I need to ask you.

868
00:36:11,569 --> 00:36:12,570
A one-centimeter atrial septal defect.

869
00:36:12,870 --> 00:36:13,671
Operated on at our hospital.

870
00:36:14,405 --> 00:36:14,872
Who did it?

871
00:36:15,673 --> 00:36:16,307
Director Sheng.

872
00:36:22,613 --> 00:36:23,714
The surgery is already done.

873
00:36:23,881 --> 00:36:24,749
Why come to me now?

874
00:36:26,150 --> 00:36:27,285
I just don't understand.

875
00:36:27,652 --> 00:36:28,252
If transcatheter closure

876
00:36:28,286 --> 00:36:29,387
could solve it,

877
00:36:29,687 --> 00:36:31,055
why perform surgery?

878
00:36:38,329 --> 00:36:39,630
Director, you wanted me?

879
00:36:40,565 --> 00:36:41,232
I have a patient here.

880
00:36:41,399 --> 00:36:41,933
Take a look.

881
00:36:46,771 --> 00:36:47,471
Only three years old.

882
00:36:47,872 --> 00:36:49,006
Severe pulmonary artery stenosis,

883
00:36:49,407 --> 00:36:50,474
patent ductus arteriosus,

884
00:36:50,908 --> 00:36:52,043
and a small atrial septal defect.

885
00:36:53,077 --> 00:36:54,512
At birth, the right ventricle

886
00:36:54,879 --> 00:36:57,348
was moderately underdeveloped.

887
00:36:57,848 --> 00:36:59,884
He underwent pulmonary balloon valvuloplasty.

888
00:37:00,718 --> 00:37:02,086
The right ventricle is still underdeveloped.

889
00:37:02,386 --> 00:37:02,787
Look.

890
00:37:03,354 --> 00:37:04,121
Right ventricular hypertrophy,

891
00:37:04,455 --> 00:37:04,956
a small cavity,

892
00:37:05,323 --> 00:37:06,157
and at the atrial level,

893
00:37:06,324 --> 00:37:07,592
the echo still shows

894
00:37:07,725 --> 00:37:08,960
a right-to-left shunt.

895
00:37:09,427 --> 00:37:10,394
I want your input

896
00:37:10,928 --> 00:37:12,330
on the surgical plan.

897
00:37:17,168 --> 00:37:18,069
In a case like this,

898
00:37:19,804 --> 00:37:20,671
we'd usually perform

899
00:37:20,705 --> 00:37:21,872
transcatheter PDA closure,

900
00:37:22,673 --> 00:37:23,774
then measure pulmonary artery pressure.

901
00:37:24,175 --> 00:37:24,909
If feasible,

902
00:37:25,142 --> 00:37:25,610
we'd perform

903
00:37:25,610 --> 00:37:26,310
a bidirectional Glenn procedure

904
00:37:26,510 --> 00:37:28,312
to complete a one-and-a-half ventricle repair.

905
00:37:29,046 --> 00:37:30,147
If postoperative oxygen saturation

906
00:37:30,147 --> 00:37:31,549
can be maintained around 90 percent,

907
00:37:32,149 --> 00:37:33,050
that can essentially be

908
00:37:33,084 --> 00:37:33,684
the definitive operation.

909
00:37:34,986 --> 00:37:36,354
I want to do a hybrid procedure.

910
00:37:36,887 --> 00:37:37,655
But this time,

911
00:37:37,788 --> 00:37:39,323
I want to use a small axillary incision.

912
00:37:39,924 --> 00:37:42,126
That would avoid splitting the sternum.

913
00:37:42,493 --> 00:37:43,194
Otherwise,

914
00:37:43,194 --> 00:37:44,028
he'll be left with a large chest scar.

915
00:37:45,229 --> 00:37:47,164
He may feel self-conscious when he grows up.

916
00:37:48,799 --> 00:37:49,266
Why?

917
00:37:49,800 --> 00:37:50,968
With a small axillary incision,

918
00:37:51,235 --> 00:37:52,403
the operative field becomes smaller.

919
00:37:52,503 --> 00:37:53,638
Dissection may be inadequate,

920
00:37:54,038 --> 00:37:54,905
which actually increases risk.

921
00:37:55,406 --> 00:37:56,107
It is very difficult.

922
00:37:56,507 --> 00:37:58,275
I remember more than ten years ago in Xinjiang,

923
00:37:58,909 --> 00:38:01,879
we held free clinics

924
00:38:02,246 --> 00:38:03,014
for children with congenital heart disease

925
00:38:03,547 --> 00:38:04,215
and performed free surgery.

926
00:38:04,315 --> 00:38:05,483
Busloads of children

927
00:38:06,050 --> 00:38:06,517
were brought in.

928
00:38:06,550 --> 00:38:07,785
We operated

929
00:38:08,252 --> 00:38:10,655
one case after another.

930
00:38:10,721 --> 00:38:11,555
We handled

931
00:38:12,123 --> 00:38:12,823
Practice makes perfect.

932
00:38:12,990 --> 00:38:13,491
Director,

933
00:38:14,325 --> 00:38:15,293
the past is the past.

934
00:38:15,926 --> 00:38:17,495
It cannot serve as the basis for today.

935
00:38:17,995 --> 00:38:19,130
Every patient

936
00:38:19,130 --> 00:38:19,930
has a different specific condition.

937
00:38:20,364 --> 00:38:21,065
For this procedure,

938
00:38:21,132 --> 00:38:22,133
I also want to avoid cardiopulmonary bypass.

939
00:38:22,767 --> 00:38:24,435
If we're going to do it,

940
00:38:31,842 --> 00:38:33,544
a hybrid procedure is already difficult enough.

941
00:38:34,545 --> 00:38:36,647
You also want a small axillary incision,

942
00:38:36,714 --> 00:38:37,715
plus an off-pump approach.

943
00:38:38,182 --> 00:38:39,283
That not only makes it more difficult,

944
00:38:39,350 --> 00:38:40,384
but also increases the risk.

945
00:38:41,052 --> 00:38:41,585
Don't worry.

946
00:38:43,120 --> 00:38:43,888
I've already invited

947
00:38:43,921 --> 00:38:44,955
pediatric specialists

948
00:38:45,456 --> 00:38:46,524
to carefully simulate

949
00:38:46,557 --> 00:38:47,692
the entire procedure.

950
00:38:48,392 --> 00:38:49,160
I'm very confident.

951
00:38:54,398 --> 00:38:55,366
A one-centimeter atrial septal defect.

952
00:38:56,167 --> 00:38:57,535
I saw the report said

953
00:38:57,635 --> 00:38:59,236
the rim was relatively soft

954
00:38:59,603 --> 00:39:00,871
and unfavorable for device closure.

955
00:39:01,405 --> 00:39:02,473
So I asked

956
00:39:02,506 --> 00:39:03,441
Pediatric Cardiology.

957
00:39:04,208 --> 00:39:05,443
But they also said

958
00:39:05,710 --> 00:39:06,510
transcatheter closure

959
00:39:06,544 --> 00:39:08,012
is very advanced now.

960
00:39:08,612 --> 00:39:09,146
The occluder

961
00:39:09,213 --> 00:39:10,281
isn't that easy to dislodge.

962
00:39:11,148 --> 00:39:12,183
I just don't understand.

963
00:39:12,583 --> 00:39:13,117
If device closure

964
00:39:13,150 --> 00:39:14,285
could solve it,

965
00:39:14,652 --> 00:39:15,920
why perform surgery?

966
00:39:17,188 --> 00:39:17,855
We all think

967
00:39:17,888 --> 00:39:18,789
he put publicity

968
00:39:18,889 --> 00:39:19,757
and spectacle

969
00:39:19,790 --> 00:39:21,025
ahead of the patient.

970
00:39:21,358 --> 00:39:22,827
His motives weren't pure.

971
00:39:24,795 --> 00:39:25,529
For this operation,

972
00:39:26,430 --> 00:39:27,565
I want you to handle the interventional part.

973
00:39:28,966 --> 00:39:30,134
You could ask Cardiology.

974
00:39:30,768 --> 00:39:31,769
I trust one of our own more.

975
00:39:37,775 --> 00:39:38,409
I know

976
00:39:38,876 --> 00:39:40,144
you have reservations

977
00:39:40,277 --> 00:39:40,945
about this plan.

978
00:39:41,879 --> 00:39:43,547
But this child is only three.

979
00:39:44,048 --> 00:39:45,282
He has a long future ahead.

980
00:39:46,550 --> 00:39:47,952
Whether it's the small axillary incision

981
00:39:47,985 --> 00:39:48,919
or the off-pump approach,

982
00:39:50,988 --> 00:39:51,922
the risk is higher,

983
00:39:52,923 --> 00:39:54,024
but so is the potential benefit.

984
00:39:55,159 --> 00:39:57,561
After surgery, he can live more like a normal child.

985
00:39:58,229 --> 00:39:58,929
For that,

986
00:39:59,597 --> 00:40:00,998
it's worth making the effort.

987
00:40:08,572 --> 00:40:08,873
All right.

988
00:40:09,507 --> 00:40:10,107
I agree.

989
00:40:12,209 --> 00:40:13,277
But I still strongly insist

990
00:40:13,310 --> 00:40:14,345
that cardiopulmonary bypass be on standby.

991
00:40:14,879 --> 00:40:16,013
If hypoxia occurs,

992
00:40:16,046 --> 00:40:16,814
we can start it immediately.

993
00:40:17,481 --> 00:40:17,948
Agreed.

994
00:40:32,730 --> 00:40:33,063
Xiao Lin,

995
00:40:34,432 --> 00:40:35,065
let me introduce you.

996
00:40:35,599 --> 00:40:36,634
This is Director Dong

997
00:40:36,767 --> 00:40:37,802
from Pediatric Cardiology

998
00:40:38,169 --> 00:40:38,969
at Dongjiang Children's Hospital.

999
00:40:39,103 --> 00:40:40,004
She'll assist you with the interventional portion.

1000
00:40:40,237 --> 00:40:41,672
Xiao Lin, our department's genius.

1001
00:40:42,473 --> 00:40:43,007
Director Lin.

1002
00:40:43,407 --> 00:40:44,008
I've heard so much about you.

1003
00:40:44,208 --> 00:40:45,075
You're too kind, Director Dong.

1004
00:40:45,309 --> 00:40:45,676
Thank you for coming.

1005
00:40:46,010 --> 00:40:46,944
Not at all. It's my duty.

1006
00:40:47,745 --> 00:40:48,312
Are you ready?

1007
00:40:48,546 --> 00:40:48,946
Almost.

1008
00:40:49,313 --> 00:40:49,880
We're counting on you.

1009
00:40:52,149 --> 00:40:52,783
Let's begin.

1010
00:40:55,786 --> 00:40:56,253
This way.

1011
00:40:56,387 --> 00:40:56,754
All right.

1012
00:40:57,121 --> 00:40:57,721
We've been waiting for you.

1013
00:40:58,856 --> 00:40:59,390
Let me introduce everyone.

1014
00:40:59,390 --> 00:41:00,124
This is Director Liu

1015
00:41:00,291 --> 00:41:01,959
from the children's hospital,

1016
00:41:02,693 --> 00:41:03,761
here to guide our work.

1017
00:41:04,428 --> 00:41:04,895
President Wang,

1018
00:41:04,962 --> 00:41:05,763
please don't say that.

1019
00:41:06,230 --> 00:41:07,264
I'm here to learn.

1020
00:41:07,331 --> 00:41:07,798
Everyone, have a seat.

1021
00:41:08,032 --> 00:41:08,465
Come on.

1022
00:41:10,534 --> 00:41:11,669
I heard from Dr. Dong

1023
00:41:11,836 --> 00:41:13,370
that she would participate in the hybrid procedure,

1024
00:41:13,771 --> 00:41:14,605
so I came along

1025
00:41:14,638 --> 00:41:15,573
to observe and learn.

1026
00:41:15,806 --> 00:41:16,173
Welcome.

1027
00:41:16,507 --> 00:41:17,274
Let me introduce

1028
00:41:17,808 --> 00:41:19,009
This is

1029
00:41:19,043 --> 00:41:19,610
Dr. Fang from our comprehensive ICU.

1030
00:41:19,743 --> 00:41:20,811
Perioperative monitoring

1031
00:41:21,045 --> 00:41:22,012
is crucial.

1032
00:41:22,680 --> 00:41:23,514
A pleasure, Director Liu.

1033
00:41:24,114 --> 00:41:24,548
Likewise.

1034
00:41:25,049 --> 00:41:26,183
Looks like I came to the right place today.

1035
00:42:01,552 --> 00:42:02,653
Xiaohu, come check the echo.

1036
00:42:09,326 --> 00:42:10,327
The occluder is well positioned.

1037
00:42:10,594 --> 00:42:11,428
No residual shunt.

1038
00:42:11,896 --> 00:42:13,264
Left pulmonary artery flow is normal.

1039
00:42:13,464 --> 00:42:14,064
Measure the pulmonary artery pressure.

1040
00:42:14,665 --> 00:42:15,065
Okay.

1041
00:42:32,850 --> 00:42:33,250
In position.

1042
00:42:48,198 --> 00:42:49,033
Mean pulmonary artery pressure:

1043
00:42:49,667 --> 00:42:50,968
fifteen... sixteen.
